Interface TargetLessTransition<X>

  • Type Parameters:
    X - target type of transition
    All Superinterfaces:
    Transition<X>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ExtraTargetLessTransition<O>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractFormUpdateTransition, AbstractTargetLessTransition, AppUserTransitionProvider.QueryRoleTransition, CreateTransition, CreatorTransition, DynamicFormTransitionProvider.Creator, DynamicFormTransitionProvider.IndexTransition, EmailTransitionProvider.CreateTransition, FormCreatorProducerTransition, FormCreatorTransition, FormUpdateProducerTransition, FormUpdateTransition, PersonalResponseTransitionProvider.CreateTransition, TableTransitionProvider.IndexTransition, TableTransitionProvider.UploadTransition

    public interface TargetLessTransition<X>
extends Transition<X>
    A transition that generates a Form to supply all input. There is no implied target. This is needed for creation forms and forms that select the target for a nested transition or that create new targets.

    The appearance of the form can be customised by implementing CustomFormContent.
